{"article_id":"64JG71NTSztU7C97","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The good news is that the George Floyd rioting is starting to die down in some parts of the country .","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Washington DC saw the National Guard move out","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"after demonstrations became more peaceful .","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"It ' s not nearly as bad as last week .","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"That ' s for sure .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"The riots were sparked by the death of George Floyd in Minneapolis on May 25 .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"It was an officer-involved fatality .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Floyd was arrested on suspicion","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"of using fake currency , a nonviolent crime .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"Floyd was unarmed .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"He was reportedly intoxicated","depth":15},{"id":11,"text":"when he was approached by police ,","depth":15},{"id":12,"text":"but that ' s immaterial .","depth":14},{"id":13,"text":"He was able to be apprehended and placed in handcuffs .","depth":14},{"id":14,"text":"As he laid prone to the ground ,","depth":15},{"id":15,"text":"Officer Derek Chauvin placed his knee on the back of his neck","depth":16},{"id":16,"text":"and kept it there for nearly ten minutes .","depth":16},{"id":17,"text":"Floyd died ,","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"but not after audible cries of him","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"saying","depth":15},{"id":20,"text":"he couldn ' t breathe .","depth":15},{"id":21,"text":"It ' s all on video .","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"Everyone was outraged .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"In fact , it ' s probably one of the few times","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"that this incident faced condemnation from across the political spectrum .","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"Chauvin was fired","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"and charged with second-degree murder .","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"The three other officers were also fired","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"and charged with aiding and abetting second-degree murder .","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"There should have been protests .","depth":8},{"id":30,"text":"There should be anger .","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"The use of force was absurd ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"but support for protests for anything go out the window","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"when looting , arson , and vandalism engulf cities .","depth":9},{"id":34,"text":"Minneapolis burned ,","depth":7},{"id":35,"text":"New York City became a total warzone ,","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"and police officers were targeted everywhere .","depth":8},{"id":37,"text":"It was mayhem .","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"Another thing","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"that was exposed","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"was the level of infiltration","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"the far left has done regarding our institutions especially the media .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"There was always a liberal bias ,","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"but this has shifted toward a new and more unhinged element .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"The New York Times ran an op-ed by Sen. Tom Cotton","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"( R-AR )","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"who argued","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"we should deploy the military","depth":13},{"id":48,"text":"to quell the mob violence .","depth":13},{"id":49,"text":"The Left erupted in outrage .","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"Reportedly , full-blown civil war erupted at the publication-and the far left won .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"The paper ' s editorial page editor resigned .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"In Philadelphia , one of the Inquirer ' s top editors was forced to resign over a column with the headline \" Buildings Matter , Too \" :","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Stan Wischnowski , the top editor of The Philadelphia Inquirer , has announced his resignation ,","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"days after discontent among the newspaper ' s staff erupted over a headline on a column about the impact of the civil unrest","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"following the police killing of George Floyd in Minneapolis .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"Wischnowski , 58 , led the paper over two turbulent periods in recent years ,","depth":6},{"id":57,"text":"driving it ; its sister paper , the Daily News ; and its website , Inquirer.com , to reshape themselves","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"as the digital age transformed the news business .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"He was key in the creation of Spotlight PA , a new multireporter team","depth":6},{"id":60,"text":"to provide news outlets across Pennsylvania with investigative coverage of state government .","depth":6},{"id":61,"text":"He also was in charge in 2011","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"when The Inquirer investigated violence within Philadelphia schools , a series","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"awarded the Pulitzer Prize for Public Service . [ ... ]","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"It was the placement of an insensitive headline over Inga Saffron ' s column in the Tuesday newspaper","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"that may have set the stage for Wischnowski ' s departure .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"He joined the two other top editors","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"in signing an apology to readers and staff ,","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"characterizing the headline , \" Buildings Matter , Too , \" as \" deeply offensive \"","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"and apologizing for it .","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"The column had explored the destruction of buildings amid the looting","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"that accompanied some of the nationwide protests over police violence .","depth":12},{"id":72,"text":"This is insanity .","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"It ' s authoritarian .","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"It ' s un-American .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"We have the woke version of blacklisting here .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"If you write something","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"they disagree with ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"you ' re destroyed .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"If they think","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"your views represent \" violence , \"","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"you ' re destroyed .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"These were the insane views","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"spouted by college leftists .","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"They ' ve graduated","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"and you see","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"where they ' ve spread their cancer .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Granted , not all liberals agree with these wingnut psychos .","depth":4},{"id":88,"text":"William Saletan of Slate doesn ' t agree with Cotton on anything ,","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"and would never have thought of defending him ever ,","depth":6},{"id":90,"text":"but he torched the Times","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"for making up criteria","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"that don ' t exist","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"to justify their reasoning","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"for coming out against it .","depth":9},{"id":95,"text":"The publication released some weak sauce note","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"that pretty much said","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"they jumped the gun .","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"They didn ' t .","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"And said","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"there were factual inaccuracies in Cotton ' s piece ,","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"but that wasn ' t true either .","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"As Saletan noted ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"it was no different than the vicious anti-Trump pieces","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"that run daily .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Cotton 's column was rather calm ,","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"to be frank .","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"It wasn ' t about \" standards . \"","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"The entire period since 2016 has been a nonstop wave of moral panic and national psychosis .","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Russiagate , MeToo , Nazi hysteria , with some countervailing panics on the Right as well .","depth":9},{"id":110,"text":"Now this .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"If you allow yourself to get sucked in ,","depth":7},{"id":112,"text":"it ' s very hard to pull yourself back out again","depth":7},{"id":113,"text":"- Michael Tracey","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"( @ mtracey )","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"June 8 , 2020","depth":6},{"id":116,"text":"The media cry-bullies said","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"that an op-ed in a newspaper was literal violence ,","depth":9},{"id":118,"text":"but then they say","depth":9},{"id":119,"text":"YOU ' RE the crazy one","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"for pointing out how crazy that logic is .","depth":10},{"id":121,"text":"I ' m actually glad","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"they popularized the term \" gaslighting \"","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"because they are the ultimate manipulative \" gaslighters \"","depth":8},{"id":124,"text":"- Michael Tracey","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"( @ mtracey )","depth":8},{"id":126,"text":"June 8 , 2020","depth":7},{"id":127,"text":"Everywhere from the New York Times , to Variety , to The Intercept , these 20 and 30-something journalist cry-bullies are successfully forcing institutions to bend to their will and accommodate their sputtering , logic-free emotional meltdowns .","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"The media industry is completely fucked","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"- Michael Tracey","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"( @ mtracey )","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"June 7 , 2020","depth":9},{"id":132,"text":"If you ' re an emotionally unstable baby","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"who regards disagreement as \" violence \"","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"journalism is probably the wrong field for you","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"- Michael Tracey","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"( @ mtracey )","depth":10},{"id":137,"text":"June 7 , 2020","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Everyone in US media","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"who offends the sensibilities of Mehdi Hasan","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"should be 